        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": ">total refactor of pyximport rather than trying to fit `importlib` to\n>old way of importing. (We will keep old pyximport for 2.7 support)\n\nSounds good to me. We could have a _pyximport2 and a fresh _pyximport3 module, and then have pyximport itself only import the right one. We would drop the ...2 version in Cython 3.1 then, and stick with the clean new module. So that's a good preparation.\n",
